text.section:
In addition to the provisions required under subsection (a) of this section, the regulations adopted by the Department shall, at a minimum:
provide for and encourage the establishment of continuing care at home programs;
for an individual who is employed by or under contract with a continuing care at home provider and who will enter a subscriber's home to provide continuing care at home services:
set minimum requirements;
require a criminal history records check, if the individual will have routine, direct access to a subscriber; and
require the provider to screen and verify the individual's character references;
establish standards for the renewal of certificates of registration;
establish standards for entrance fees, deposits, and the number of executed agreements necessary to begin operations;
establish conditions for the release of deposits and entrance fees from escrow accounts;
establish standards for when and how a subscriber or provider may rescind a continuing care at home agreement before continuing care at home services are provided to the subscriber;
allow a subscriber to rescind a continuing care at home agreement at any time if the terms of the agreement violate this subtitle; and
establish that a provider may terminate an agreement or discharge a subscriber only for just cause and establish procedures to carry out the termination or discharge.
